Package: tailor
Type: Package
Title: Tool for Adapter-domain Identification and Linking Of RBPs
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("András", "Asbóth", role = c("aut", "cre"),
        email = "sbthandras+bioinfo@gmail.com",
        comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0001-2284-412X")),
    person("Tamás", "Stirling", role = "aut",
        comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8964-6443")))
Description: Bacteriophages (phages) are viruses that infect bacteria. Many 
    phages encode receptor binding proteins (RBPs) that mediate attachment to 
    their bacterial hosts. Most RBPs contain a conserved N-terminal domain (we 
    refer to this as an "adapter") which anchors the protein to the phage 
    particle. This package provides functions to indentify these adapters and 
    group them based on sequence similarity.
